  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html>\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<title>Bubble Sort Interactive - Minimal Interface</title>\n<style>\n/* Extremely minimal styling: black text on white background, basic layout only */\nbody { margin: 12px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #000; background: #fff; }\nh1 { font-size: 18px; margin: 6px 0; }\nlabel { display: inline-block; margin: 4px 6px 4px 0; }\n.section { margin: 8px 0; padding: 6px 0; border-top: 1px solid #000; }\n.array-input { margin-top: 6px; }\n.array-item { width: 52px; padding: 4px; margin-right: 4px; }\n.controls { margin-top: 8px; }\n.small { font-size: 13px; }\n.listbox { width: 100%; max-height: 180px; overflow: auto; border: 1px solid #000; padding: 4px; }\n.btn { margin: 2px; }\n.step-list-item { padding: 2px 4px; cursor: pointer; border-bottom: 1px dashed #000; }\n.step-list-item.selected { font-weight: bold; }\n.flex-row { display: flex; gap: 8px; align-items: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }\n.grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; }\ntextarea { width: 100%; height: 60px; }\nfieldset { padding: 6px; margin: 6px 0; }\n.note { font-size: 12px; margin-top: 6px; }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h1>Bubble Sort Interactive (Minimal UI)</h1>\n<p class=\"small\">This page lets you explore Bubble Sort deeply. Edit data, generate traces, step forward/back in micro-steps (compare, swap), autoplay, set breakpoints, export/import states, and inspect a complete execution trace. Visuals are intentionally minimal.</p>\n\n<div class=\"section\">\n  <strong>Array Setup</strong>\n  <div class=\"array-input\">\n    <label>Array (comma or space separated):</label>\n    <input id=\"arrayText\" type=\"text\" size=\"60\" value=\"5,3,8,4,2,7,1\">\n    <button id=\"applyArray\" class=\"btn\">Apply</button>\n    <button id=\"useCurrent\" class=\"btn\">Use Current</button>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"flex-row controls\">\n    <label>Size:\n      <input id=\"sizeSlider\" type=\"range\" min=\"2\" max=\"30\" value=\"7\">\n    </label>\n    <label>Randomize size:\n      <button id=\"randomizeBtn\" class=\"btn\">Randomize</button>\n    </label>\n    <label>Min:\n      <input id=\"minVal\" type=\"number\" value=\"0\" style=\"width:70px\">\n    </label>\n    <label>Max:\n      <input id=\"maxVal\" type=\"number\" value=\"10\" style=\"width:70px\">\n    </label>\n    <label>\n      <button id=\"sortedBtn\" class=\"btn\">Fill Sorted</button>\n    </label>\n    <label>\n      <button id=\"reverseBtn\" class=\"btn\">Fill Reverse</button>\n    </label>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"note small\">After applying a new array you must \"Recompute Trace\" to update the instrumented steps. \"Use Current\" fills the text input with the currently displayed snapshot.</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"section\">\n  <strong>Options</strong>\n  <div class=\"flex-row\">\n    <label>Order:\n      <select id=\"orderSelect\">\n        <option value=\"asc\">Ascending</option>\n        <option value=\"desc\">Descending</option>\n      </select>\n    </label>\n    <label><input id=\"optimizeTail\" type=\"checkbox\"> Early exit if no swaps (optimized)</label>\n    <label><input id=\"showCompare\" type=\"checkbox\" checked> Show comparisons in trace</label>\n    <label><input id=\"microStep\" type=\"checkbox\" checked> Micro-step (compare then swap)</label>\n    <label><input id=\"indexing1\" type=\"checkbox\"> 1-based indices in labels</label>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"flex-row\">\n    <label>Play speed (ms per step): <input id=\"speed\" type=\"range\" min=\"50\" max=\"2000\" value=\"300\"></label>\n    <label>Auto-play mode:\n      <select id=\"autoplayMode\">\n        <option value=\"normal\">Normal</option>\n        <option value=\"untilSwap\">Run until next swap</option>\n        <option value=\"untilCompare\">Run until next compare</option>\n      </select>\n    </label>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"section\">\n  <strong>Controls</strong>\n  <div class=\"flex-row\">\n    <button id=\"recompute\" class=\"btn\">Recompute Trace</button>\n    <button id=\"rewind\" class=\"btn\">Rewind (start)</button>\n    <button id=\"stepBack\" class=\"btn\">Step Back</button>\n    <button id=\"stepForward\" class=\"btn\">Step Forward</button>\n    <button id=\"playPause\" class=\"btn\">Play</button>\n    <button id=\"fastForward\" class=\"btn\">Fast Forward (end)</button>\n    <button id=\"resetBtn\" class=\"btn\">Reset (initial)</button>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"note small\">Play will follow the computed trace. If you edit the array while running, press \"Recompute Trace\" to regenerate steps from the edited initial state.</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"section grid\">\n  <div>\n    <strong>Array Visualization (Editable)</strong>\n    <div id=\"arrayContainer\" style=\"margin-top:6px\"></div>\n    <div class=\"flex-row\" style=\"margin-top:8px\">\n      <button id=\"insertLeft\" class=\"btn\">Insert Left</button>\n      <button id=\"insertRight\" class=\"btn\">Insert Right</button>\n      <button id=\"removeLast\" class=\"btn\">Remove Last</button>\n      <button id=\"normalize\" class=\"btn\">Normalize (integers)</button>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"note small\">Each value is a number. Edit values directly and click \"Recompute Trace\" to analyze.</div>\n    <fieldset>\n      <legend class=\"small\">Breakpoints</legend>\n      <label>Type:\n        <select id=\"bpType\">\n          <option value=\"index\">At compare j index</option>\n          <option value=\"onSwap\">On any swap</option>\n          <option value=\"compareCount\">When comparisons &gt;=</option>\n        </select>\n      </label>\n      <input id=\"bpValue\" type=\"number\" style=\"width: 80px;\">\n      <button id=\"addBreakpoint\" class=\"btn\">Add</button>\n      <div id=\"breakpointList\" class=\"listbox\" style=\"margin-top:8px\"></div>\n    </fieldset>\n  </div>\n\n  <div>\n    <strong>Trace & Execution</strong>\n    <div>Current step: <span id=\"currentStep\">0</span> / <span id=\"totalSteps\">0</span></div>\n    <div>Action: <span id=\"currentAction\">-</span></div>\n    <div>i: <span id=\"statI\">-</span>  j: <span id=\"statJ\">-</span></div>\n    <div>Comparisons: <span id=\"statComparisons\">0</span>  Swaps: <span id=\"statSwaps\">0</span>  Passes: <span id=\"statPasses\">0</span></div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:6px\">\n      <input id=\"traceFilter\" placeholder=\"Filter steps (swap, compare, pass, early_exit)\"/>\n      <button id=\"applyFilter\" class=\"btn\">Apply</button>\n      <button id=\"clearFilter\" class=\"btn\">Clear</button>\n    </div>\n    <div id=\"traceList\" class=\"listbox\" style=\"margin-top:8px\"></div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:6px\">\n      <label><input id=\"autoScroll\" type=\"checkbox\" checked> Auto-scroll trace to current</label>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"section\">\n  <strong>Export / Import / Save</strong>\n  <div class=\"flex-row\">\n    <button id=\"exportConfig\" class=\"btn\">Export Config</button>\n    <button id=\"exportTrace\" class=\"btn\">Export Full Trace</button>\n    <button id=\"importBtn\" class=\"btn\">Import JSON</button>\n    <button id=\"saveLocal\" class=\"btn\">Save to Local</button>\n    <button id=\"loadLocal\" class=\"btn\">Load from Local</button>\n    <select id=\"localList\"></select>\n    <button id=\"deleteLocal\" class=\"btn\">Delete Saved</button>\n  </div>\n  <textarea id=\"jsonArea\" placeholder=\"Exported JSON will appear here or paste JSON here to import.\"></textarea>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"section\">\n  <strong>Explanation / Hints</strong>\n  <div class=\"note small\">\n    - Trace entries are micro-steps: \"compare\" indicates a comparison of elements at j and j+1. If a swap is needed, a following \"swap\" step shows the array after swapping. If no swap, a \"no-swap\" step may appear if micro-step is enabled. Each pass_end marks the end of an outer loop pass.\n    <br>- Use breakpoints to pause when interesting events occur.\n    <br>- You can jump to any trace step by clicking it in the trace list. Use \"Recompute Trace\" after changing initial array or options.\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<script>\n// Minimal but feature-rich bubble sort explorer.\n// State\nlet state = {\n  initialArray: [],\n  trace: [],\n  currentIndex: 0,\n  running: false,\n  timer: null,\n  options: {\n    order: 'asc',\n    optimizeTail: true,\n    microStep: true,\n    showCompare: true,\n  },\n  stats: { comparisons: 0, swaps: 0, passes: 0 },\n  breakpoints: [], // {type:'index'|'onSwap'|'compareCount', value: number}\n  filterText: '',\n  savedLocal: {}\n};\n\n// Utility\nfunction deepCopyArray(a){ return a.slice(); }\nfunction clamp(v,min,max){ return Math.max(min,Math.min(max,v)); }\nfunction parseArrayText(s){\n  if(!s) return [];\n  let parts = s.split(/[,;\\s]+/).filter(p=>p.length>0);\n  let arr = parts.map(p=>{\n    let n = Number(p);\n    if(Number.isFinite(n)) return n;\n    // try parseInt fallback\n    let ni = parseInt(p,10);\n    if(!isNaN(ni)) return ni;\n    return 0;\n  });\n  return arr;\n}\nfunction arrayToText(a){ return a.join(', '); }\n\n// DOM references\nconst arrayText = document.getElementById('arrayText');\nconst applyArray = document.getElementById('applyArray');\nconst useCurrent = document.getElementById('useCurrent');\nconst sizeSlider = document.getElementById('sizeSlider');\nconst randomizeBtn = document.getElementById('randomizeBtn');\nconst minVal = document.getElementById('minVal');\nconst maxVal = document.getElementById('maxVal');\nconst sortedBtn = document.getElementById('sortedBtn');\nconst reverseBtn = document.getElementById('reverseBtn');\nconst recompute = document.getElementById('recompute');\nconst rewind = document.getElementById('rewind');\nconst stepBack = document.getElementById('stepBack');\nconst stepForward = document.getElementById('stepForward');\nconst playPause = document.getElementById('playPause');\nconst fastForward = document.getElementById('fastForward');\nconst resetBtn = document.getElementById('resetBtn');\n\nconst arrayContainer = document.getElementById('arrayContainer');\nconst insertLeft = document.getElementById('insertLeft');\nconst insertRight = document.getElementById('insertRight');\nconst removeLast = document.getElementById('removeLast');\nconst normalizeBtn = document.getElementById('normalize');\n\nconst orderSelect = document.getElementById('orderSelect');\nconst optimizeTail = document.getElementById('optimizeTail');\nconst showCompare = document.getElementById('showCompare');\nconst microStep = document.getElementById('microStep');\nconst indexing1 = document.getElementById('indexing1');\n\nconst bpType = document.getElementById('bpType');\nconst bpValue = document.getElementById('bpValue');\nconst addBreakpoint = document.getElementById('addBreakpoint');\nconst breakpointList = document.getElementById('breakpointList');\n\nconst speed = document.getElementById('speed');\nconst autoplayMode = document.getElementById('autoplayMode');\n\nconst traceList = document.getElementById('traceList');\nconst currentStep = document.getElementById('currentStep');\nconst totalSteps = document.getElementById('totalSteps');\nconst currentAction = document.getElementById('currentAction');\nconst statI = document.getElementById('statI');\nconst statJ = document.getElementById('statJ');\nconst statComparisons = document.getElementById('statComparisons');\nconst statSwaps = document.getElementById('statSwaps');\nconst statPasses = document.getElementById('statPasses');\nconst traceFilter = document.getElementById('traceFilter');\nconst applyFilter = document.getElementById('applyFilter');\nconst clearFilter = document.getElementById('clearFilter');\nconst autoScroll = document.getElementById('autoScroll');\n\nconst exportConfig = document.getElementById('exportConfig');\nconst exportTrace = document.getElementById('exportTrace');\nconst importBtn = document.getElementById('importBtn');\nconst jsonArea = document.getElementById('jsonArea');\nconst saveLocal = document.getElementById('saveLocal');\nconst loadLocal = document.getElementById('loadLocal');\nconst localList = document.getElementById('localList');\nconst deleteLocal = document.getElementById('deleteLocal');\n\n// Initialization\nfunction init(){\n  // apply initial array from input\n  state.initialArray = parseArrayText(arrayText.value);\n  renderArrayInputs(state.initialArray);\n  loadSavedList();\n  attachListeners();\n  recomputeTrace(); // initial trace\n  updateUI();\n}\nfunction attachListeners(){\n  applyArray.addEventListener('click', ()=> {\n    let arr = parseArrayText(arrayText.value);\n    state.initialArray = arr;\n    renderArrayInputs(arr);\n    recomputeTrace();\n  });\n  useCurrent.addEventListener('click', ()=>{\n    let arr = readArrayInputs();\n    arrayText.value = arrayToText(arr);\n  });\n  sizeSlider.addEventListener('input', ()=> {\n    let n = Number(sizeSlider.value);\n    let min = Number(minVal.value) || 0;\n    let max = Number(maxVal.value) || 10;\n    let arr = randomArray(n, min, max);\n    arrayText.value = arrayToText(arr);\n    state.initialArray = arr;\n    renderArrayInputs(arr);\n  });\n  randomizeBtn.addEventListener('click', ()=> {\n    let n = Number(sizeSlider.value);\n    let min = Number(minVal.value) || 0;\n    let max = Number(maxVal.value) || 10;\n    let arr = randomArray(n, min, max);\n    arrayText.value = arrayToText(arr);\n    state.initialArray = arr;\n    renderArrayInputs(arr);\n    recomputeTrace();\n  });\n  sortedBtn.addEventListener('click', ()=> {\n    let n = Number(sizeSlider.value);\n    let min = Number(minVal.value) || 0;\n    let max = Number(maxVal.value) || min + n - 1;\n    let arr = [];\n    for(let i=0;i<n;i++) arr.push(min + i);\n    arrayText.value = arrayToText(arr);\n    state.initialArray = arr;\n    renderArrayInputs(arr);\n    recomputeTrace();\n  });\n  reverseBtn.addEventListener('click', ()=> {\n    let n = Number(sizeSlider.value);\n    let min = Number(minVal.value) || 0;\n    let arr = [];\n    for(let i=0;i<n;i++) arr.push(min + (n - i));\n    arrayText.value = arrayToText(arr);\n    state.initialArray = arr;\n    renderArrayInputs(arr);\n    recomputeTrace();\n  });\n  recompute.addEventListener('click', ()=> recomputeTrace());\n  rewind.addEventListener('click', ()=> { jumpTo(0); pauseExecution(); });\n  stepBack.addEventListener('click', ()=> { stepBackOne(); });\n  stepForward.addEventListener('click', ()=> { stepForwardOne(); });\n  playPause.addEventListener('click', ()=> { togglePlayPause(); });\n  fastForward.addEventListener('click', ()=> { jumpTo(state.trace.length - 1); pauseExecution(); });\n  resetBtn.addEventListener('click', ()=> { resetToInitial(); });\n\n  insertLeft.addEventListener('click', ()=> { insertAt(0,0); });\n  insertRight.addEventListener('click', ()=> { insertAt(-1,0); });\n  removeLast.addEventListener('click', ()=> { removeLastItem(); });\n  normalizeBtn.addEventListener('click', ()=> { normalizeArrayInputs(); });\n\n  orderSelect.addEventListener('change', ()=> { state.options.order = orderSelect.value; });\n  optimizeTail.addEventListener('change', ()=> { state.options.optimizeTail = optimizeTail.checked; });\n  showCompare.addEventListener('change', ()=> { state.options.showCompare = showCompare.checked; });\n  microStep.addEventListener('change', ()=> { state.options.microStep = microStep.checked; });\n  indexing1.addEventListener('change', ()=> { renderTraceList(); });\n\n  addBreakpoint.addEventListener('click', ()=> { addBreakpointAction(); });\n\n  applyFilter.addEventListener('click', ()=> { state.filterText = traceFilter.value.trim(); renderTraceList(); });\n  clearFilter.addEventListener('click', ()=> { traceFilter.value = ''; state.filterText = ''; renderTraceList(); });\n\n  exportConfig.addEventListener('click', ()=> exportConfigAction());\n  exportTrace.addEventListener('click', ()=> exportTraceAction());\n  importBtn.addEventListener('click', ()=> importAction());\n  saveLocal.addEventListener('click', ()=> saveToLocal());\n  loadLocal.addEventListener('click', ()=> loadFromLocal());\n  localList.addEventListener('change', ()=> {/* no-op */});\n  deleteLocal.addEventListener('click', ()=> deleteLocalSave());\n}\n\nfunction randomArray(n, min, max){\n  min = Number(min) || 0;\n  max = Number(max) || (min + n);\n  if(max < min) { let t = max; max = min; min = t; }\n  let arr = [];\n  for(let i=0;i<n;i++){\n    let r = Math.floor(Math.random() * (max - min + 1)) + min;\n    arr.push(r);\n  }\n  return arr;\n}\n\nfunction renderArrayInputs(arr){\n  arrayContainer.innerHTML = '';\n  arr.forEach((v,i)=>{\n    let input = document.createElement('input');\n    input.type = 'number';\n    input.value = v;\n    input.className = 'array-item';\n    input.dataset.index = i;\n    input.addEventListener('change', ()=> {\n      // update initialArray immediately but require recompute to re-generate trace\n      let idx = Number(input.dataset.index);\n      let val = Number(input.value) || 0;\n      state.initialArray[idx] = val;\n    });\n    arrayContainer.appendChild(input);\n  });\n  // if empty, provide at least two inputs\n  if(arr.length === 0){\n    for(let i=0;i<2;i++){\n      let input = document.createElement('input');\n      input.type = 'number';\n      input.value = 0;\n      input.className = 'array-item';\n      input.dataset.index = i;\n      input.addEventListener('change', ()=> {\n        let idx = Number(input.dataset.index);\n        state.initialArray[idx] = Number(input.value) || 0;\n      });\n      arrayContainer.appendChild(input);\n    }\n    state.initialArray = [0,0];\n  }\n}\n\nfunction readArrayInputs(){\n  let inputs = arrayContainer.querySelectorAll('input.array-item');\n  let arr = [];\n  inputs.forEach(inp => {\n    let n = Number(inp.value);\n    if(!Number.isFinite(n)) n = 0;\n    arr.push(n);\n  });\n  return arr;\n}\n\nfunction insertAt(pos, value){\n  let arr = readArrayInputs();\n  if(pos < 0) arr.push(value);\n  else arr.splice(pos, 0, value);\n  state.initialArray = arr;\n  arrayText.value = arrayToText(arr);\n  renderArrayInputs(arr);\n}\n\nfunction removeLastItem(){\n  let arr = readArrayInputs();\n  if(arr.length > 1) arr.pop();\n  state.initialArray = arr;\n  arrayText.value = arrayToText(arr);\n  renderArrayInputs(arr);\n}\n\nfunction normalizeArrayInputs(){\n  let arr = readArrayInputs().map(v=> Math.round(Number(v) || 0));\n  state.initialArray = arr;\n  arrayText.value = arrayToText(arr);\n  renderArrayInputs(arr);\n}\n\n// Trace generation\nfunction recomputeTrace(){\n  // read options\n  state.options.order = orderSelect.value;\n  state.options.optimizeTail = optimizeTail.checked;\n  state.options.microStep = microStep.checked;\n  state.options.showCompare = showCompare.checked;\n  // read array inputs to make sure initialArray is up to date\n  state.initialArray = readArrayInputs();\n  arrayText.value = arrayToText(state.initialArray);\n  generateTrace(state.initialArray, state.options);\n  jumpTo(0);\n  updateUI();\n}\n\nfunction generateTrace(arr, options){\n  // produce instrumented micro-step trace for bubble sort\n  let a = deepCopyArray(arr);\n  let n = a.length;\n  let trace = [];\n  let comparisons = 0;\n  let swaps = 0;\n  let passes = 0;\n  let order = options.order === 'asc' ? 1 : -1; // 1 means a[j] > a[j+1] => swap for asc\n  if(n <= 1){\n    trace.push(makeStep(a, -1, -1, 'done', comparisons, swaps, passes));\n    state.trace = trace;\n    state.stats = {comparisons, swaps, passes};\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Outer loop\n  for(let i=0;i<n-1;i++){\n    passes++;\n    let swappedInPass = false;\n    let limit = options.optimizeTail ? (n - i - 1) : (n - 1);\n    for(let j=0;j<limit;j++){\n      // compare step\n      comparisons++;\n      let shouldSwap = (a[j] - a[j+1]) * order > 0;\n      let stepCompare = makeStep(a, i, j, 'compare', comparisons, swaps, passes, {comparePair:[j,j+1], shouldSwap});\n      if(options.showCompare) trace.push(stepCompare);\n      // On micro-step mode: add decision steps\n      if(options.microStep){\n        if(shouldSwap){\n          // swap step: produce a copy after swap\n          let copyBefore = deepCopyArray(a);\n          // perform swap in the working array\n          let tmp = a[j]; a[j] = a[j+1]; a[j+1] = tmp;\n          swaps++;\n          swappedInPass = true;\n          trace.push(makeStep(a, i, j, 'swap', comparisons, swaps, passes, {comparePair:[j,j+1], before: copyBefore}));\n        } else {\n          trace.push(makeStep(a, i, j, 'no-swap', comparisons, swaps, passes, {comparePair:[j,j+1]}));\n        }\n      } else {\n        // If not micro-step, perform swap immediately in working array and push a combined 'compare-swap' step if swap happened\n        if(shouldSwap){\n          let copyBefore = deepCopyArray(a);\n          let tmp = a[j]; a[j] = a[j+1]; a[j+1] = tmp;\n          swaps++;\n          swappedInPass = true;\n          trace.push(makeStep(a, i, j, 'compare+swap', comparisons, swaps, passes, {comparePair:[j,j+1], before: copyBefore}));\n        } else {\n          // still record compare outcome if showCompare\n          if(!options.showCompare){\n            // if showCompare disabled and microStep false, produce a minimal step to indicate progress\n            trace.push(makeStep(a, i, j, 'compare', comparisons, swaps, passes, {comparePair:[j,j+1], shouldSwap:false}));\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n    // end of pass\n    trace.push(makeStep(a, i, -1, 'pass_end', comparisons, swaps, passes));\n    if(!swappedInPass && options.optimizeTail){\n      trace.push(makeStep(a, i, -1, 'early_exit', comparisons, swaps, passes));\n      break;\n    }\n  }\n  // final done\n  trace.push(makeStep(a, -1, -1, 'done', comparisons, swaps, passes));\n  state.trace = trace;\n  state.stats = {comparisons, swaps, passes};\n}\n\nfunction makeStep(arraySnapshot, i, j, action, comparisons, swaps, passes, meta){\n  return {\n    array: deepCopyArray(arraySnapshot),\n    i: i,\n    j: j,\n    action: action,\n    comparisons: comparisons,\n    swaps: swaps,\n    passes: passes,\n    meta: meta || null,\n    time: Date.now()\n  };\n}\n\n// Rendering trace and stepping\nfunction renderTraceList(){\n  traceList.innerHTML = '';\n  let filter = (state.filterText || '').toLowerCase();\n  state.trace.forEach((step, idx) => {\n    let label = `${idx}: ${step.action}`;\n    if(step.action === 'compare' && step.meta && step.meta.comparePair){\n      label += ` [${step.meta.comparePair[0]},${step.meta.comparePair[1]}]`;\n    } else if(step.action === 'swap' && step.meta && step.meta.comparePair){\n      label += ` [swap ${step.meta.comparePair[0]},${step.meta.comparePair[1]}]`;\n    } else if(step.action === 'compare+swap'){\n      label += ` [swap ${step.meta.comparePair[0]},${step.meta.comparePair[1]}]`;\n    }\n    if(indexing1.checked && step.meta && step.meta.comparePair){\n      label = `${idx}: ${step.action} [${step.meta.comparePair[0]+1},${step.meta.comparePair[1]+1}]`;\n    }\n    if(filter && label.toLowerCase().indexOf(filter) === -1) return;\n    let div = document.createElement('div');\n    div.className = 'step-list-item' + (idx === state.currentIndex ? ' selected' : '');\n    div.textContent = label;\n    div.dataset.idx = idx;\n    div.addEventListener('click', ()=> { jumpTo(idx); pauseExecution(); });\n    traceList.appendChild(div);\n  });\n  totalSteps.textContent = state.trace.length - 1;\n  currentStep.textContent = state.currentIndex;\n  if(autoScroll.checked){\n    // Scroll the selected element into view\n    let selected = traceList.querySelector('.step-list-item.selected');\n    if(selected) selected.scrollIntoView({block:'nearest'});\n  }\n}\n\nfunction updateUI(){\n  // update array display to current trace snapshot\n  let step = state.trace[state.currentIndex];\n  if(step){\n    renderArrayInputs(step.array);\n    currentAction.textContent = step.action;\n    statI.textContent = (step.i >= 0 ? step.i : '-');\n    statJ.textContent = (step.j >= 0 ? step.j : '-');\n    statComparisons.textContent = step.comparisons;\n    statSwaps.textContent = step.swaps;\n    statPasses.textContent = step.passes;\n  } else {\n    renderArrayInputs(state.initialArray);\n    currentAction.textContent = '-';\n    statI.textContent = '-';\n    statJ.textContent = '-';\n    statComparisons.textContent = state.stats.comparisons || 0;\n    statSwaps.textContent = state.stats.swaps || 0;\n    statPasses.textContent = state.stats.passes || 0;\n  }\n  currentStep.textContent = state.currentIndex;\n  totalSteps.textContent = Math.max(0, state.trace.length - 1);\n  renderTraceList();\n  updateBreakpointsList();\n  playPause.textContent = state.running ? 'Pause' : 'Play';\n}\n\nfunction jumpTo(idx){\n  if(idx < 0) idx = 0;\n  if(idx >= state.trace.length) idx = state.trace.length - 1;\n  state.currentIndex = idx;\n  updateUI();\n}\n\nfunction stepForwardOne(){\n  if(state.currentIndex < state.trace.length - 1){\n    state.currentIndex++;\n    updateUI();\n    // If autoplay mode indicates break until next swap and we just reached a swap, auto-pause handled in play loop\n  }\n  // If at end, pause\n  if(state.currentIndex >= state.trace.length - 1) pauseExecution();\n}\n\nfunction stepBackOne(){\n  if(state.currentIndex > 0){\n    state.currentIndex--;\n    updateUI();\n  }\n}\n\nfunction togglePlayPause(){\n  if(state.running) pauseExecution();\n  else startExecution();\n}\n\nfunction startExecution(){\n  if(state.trace.length === 0) return;\n  state.running = true;\n  playPause.textContent = 'Pause';\n  runLoop();\n}\n\nfunction pauseExecution(){\n  state.running = false;\n  playPause.textContent = 'Play';\n  if(state.timer){ clearTimeout(state.timer); state.timer = null; }\n}\n\nfunction runLoop(){\n  if(!state.running) return;\n  // Determine next step based on autoplay mode and breakpoints\n  let delay = Number(speed.value) || 300;\n  let mode = autoplayMode.value;\n  // When mode is 'untilSwap' or 'untilCompare' we should advance until a condition, pausing when condition met.\n  if(mode === 'normal'){\n    // step one and check for breakpoint\n    stepForwardOne();\n    if(checkBreakpoints(state.trace[state.currentIndex])){\n      // pause before the step or after? We'll pause after arriving at the matching step.\n      pauseExecution();\n      return;\n    }\n    if(state.currentIndex >= state.trace.length - 1){\n      pauseExecution();\n      return;\n    }\n    state.timer = setTimeout(runLoop, delay);\n  } else if(mode === 'untilSwap' || mode === 'untilCompare'){\n    // keep stepping until condition matches or end\n    let shouldStop = false;\n    while(!shouldStop && state.currentIndex < state.trace.length - 1){\n      stepForwardOne();\n      let step = state.trace[state.currentIndex];\n      if(checkBreakpoints(step)){\n        pauseExecution();\n        return;\n      }\n      if(mode === 'untilSwap' && (step.action === 'swap' || step.action === 'compare+swap')) {\n        shouldStop = true;\n        break;\n      }\n      if(mode === 'untilCompare' && (step.action === 'compare' || step.action === 'compare+swap')) {\n        shouldStop = true;\n        break;\n      }\n      // Small delay per iteration to allow UI responsiveness; but since we loop in JS, we need to yield\n      // We'll break to schedule next chunk\n      if(state.currentIndex < state.trace.length - 1){\n        // continue in next tick\n        state.timer = setTimeout(runLoop, delay);\n        return;\n      }\n    }\n    // Stop if condition found or at end\n    pauseExecution();\n  } else {\n    // fallback\n    stepForwardOne();\n    state.timer = setTimeout(runLoop, delay);\n  }\n}\n\nfunction checkBreakpoints(step){\n  if(!step) return false;\n  for(let bp of state.breakpoints){\n    if(bp.type === 'onSwap'){\n      if(step.action === 'swap' || step.action === 'compare+swap') return true;\n    } else if(bp.type === 'index'){\n      if(step.meta && step.meta.comparePair && (step.meta.comparePair[0] === bp.value || step.meta.comparePair[1] === bp.value)) return true;\n      // Also check j if present\n      if(step.j === bp.value) return true;\n    } else if(bp.type === 'compareCount'){\n      if(step.comparisons >= bp.value) return true;\n    }\n  }\n  return false;\n}\n\n// Breakpoints management\nfunction addBreakpointAction(){\n  let type = bpType.value;\n  let val = Number(bpValue.value);\n  if(type === 'index'){\n    if(!Number.isFinite(val)) { alert('Provide index number'); return; }\n    state.breakpoints.push({type:'index', value: val});\n  } else if(type === 'onSwap'){\n    state.breakpoints.push({type:'onSwap', value: null});\n  } else if(type === 'compareCount'){\n    if(!Number.isFinite(val)) { alert('Provide number of comparisons threshold'); return; }\n    state.breakpoints.push({type:'compareCount', value: val});\n  }\n  updateBreakpointsList();\n}\n\nfunction updateBreakpointsList(){\n  breakpointList.innerHTML = '';\n  state.breakpoints.forEach((bp, idx) => {\n    let d = document.createElement('div');\n    let txt = '';\n    if(bp.type === 'index') txt = `At index ${bp.value}`;\n    else if(bp.type === 'onSwap') txt = `On any swap`;\n    else if(bp.type === 'compareCount') txt = `When comparisons >= ${bp.value}`;\n    d.textContent = `${idx}: ${txt}`;\n    let btn = document.createElement('button');\n    btn.textContent = 'Remove';\n    btn.className = 'btn';\n    btn.style.marginLeft = '6px';\n    btn.addEventListener('click', ()=> {\n      state.breakpoints.splice(idx,1);\n      updateBreakpointsList();\n    });\n    d.appendChild(btn);\n    breakpointList.appendChild(d);\n  });\n}\n\n// Export / Import\nfunction exportConfigAction(){\n  let data = {\n    initialArray: state.initialArray,\n    options: state.options,\n    breakpoints: state.breakpoints\n  };\n  jsonArea.value = JSON.stringify(data, null, 2);\n}\n\nfunction exportTraceAction(){\n  jsonArea.value = JSON.stringify({trace: state.trace}, null, 2);\n}\n\nfunction importAction(){\n  try{\n    let obj = JSON.parse(jsonArea.value);\n    if(obj.initialArray){\n      state.initialArray = obj.initialArray.slice();\n      arrayText.value = arrayToText(state.initialArray);\n      renderArrayInputs(state.initialArray);\n      if(obj.options){\n        state.options = Object.assign(state.options, obj.options);\n        orderSelect.value = state.options.order;\n        optimizeTail.checked = !!state.options.optimizeTail;\n        showCompare.checked = !!state.options.showCompare;\n        microStep.checked = !!state.options.microStep;\n      }\n      state.breakpoints = obj.breakpoints || [];\n      recomputeTrace();\n    } else if(obj.trace){\n      // import trace - set current trace directly\n      state.trace = obj.trace;\n      state.currentIndex = 0;\n      updateUI();\n    } else {\n      alert('JSON did not contain initialArray or trace. Provide a config or a trace.');\n    }\n  }catch(e){\n    alert('Invalid JSON: ' + e.message);\n  }\n}\n\n// Local Storage Save/Load\nfunction saveToLocal(){\n  let name = prompt('Enter a name to save current config (array+options):', 'bubble-config');\n  if(!name) return;\n  let data = {\n    initialArray: state.initialArray,\n    options: state.options,\n    breakpoints: state.breakpoints,\n    timestamp: Date.now()\n  };\n  localStorage.setItem('bubblesave:' + name, JSON.stringify(data));\n  loadSavedList();\n}\n\nfunction loadSavedList(){\n  localList.innerHTML = '';\n  let keys = [];\n  for(let i=0;i<localStorage.length;i++){\n    let k = localStorage.key(i);\n    if(k && k.startsWith('bubblesave:')) keys.push(k);\n  }\n  keys.sort();\n  keys.forEach(k=>{\n    let name = k.replace('bubblesave:','');\n    let opt = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem(k) || '{}');\n    let optText = name + ' (' + new Date(opt.timestamp || Date.now()).toLocaleString() + ')';\n    let o = document.createElement('option');\n    o.value = k;\n    o.textContent = optText;\n    localList.appendChild(o);\n  });\n}\n\nfunction loadFromLocal(){\n  let sel = localList.value;\n  if(!sel){ alert('Pick a saved item from the dropdown'); return; }\n  let obj = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem(sel) || '{}');\n  if(obj.initialArray){\n    state.initialArray = obj.initialArray.slice();\n    arrayText.value = arrayToText(state.initialArray);\n    renderArrayInputs(state.initialArray);\n    state.options = Object.assign(state.options, obj.options || {});\n    orderSelect.value = state.options.order;\n    optimizeTail.checked = !!state.options.optimizeTail;\n    showCompare.checked = !!state.options.showCompare;\n    microStep.checked = !!state.options.microStep;\n    state.breakpoints = obj.breakpoints || [];\n    recomputeTrace();\n  }\n}\n\nfunction deleteLocalSave(){\n  let sel = localList.value;\n  if(!sel) { alert('Select a saved item to delete'); return; }\n  if(confirm('Delete saved item?')) {\n    localStorage.removeItem(sel);\n    loadSavedList();\n  }\n}\n\nfunction resetToInitial(){\n  // sets the working display back to the initial array and recompute trace\n  state.initialArray = parseArrayText(arrayText.value);\n  renderArrayInputs(state.initialArray);\n  recomputeTrace();\n  pauseExecution();\n}\n\n// Initialization call\ninit();\n\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
